data.meta_description: Elisa Izquierdo was a beautiful little girl born to Gustavo Izquierdo and Awilda Lopez. Gustavo, a Cuban immigrant, came to America in May of 1980 to teach dance. He took a job as a community aide in a homeless shelter in the Fort Greene section of Brooklyn,NY. In 1987 he met Awilda Lopez, a shelter resident with a...
